5000|$|For many purposes, {{the threads}} as spun by the ring frame or the mule {{are ready for}} the manufacturer; but where extra {{strength}} or smoothness is required, as in threads for sewing, crocheting, hosiery, lace and carpets; also where multicoloured effects are needed, as in <b>Grandrelle,</b> or some special form of irregularity, as in corkscrewed, and knopped yarns, two or more single threads are compounded and twisted together. This operation is known as [...] "doubling".|$|E

